Language: Haida
Language code: hdn
Lines: translit translit-seg gloss translat
Author: Roman Pearah & Kristen Piepgrass
Date: January 14, 2016
Source a: Enrico, John. Haida Syntax. Lincoln: University of Nebraska Press, 2003. Print.

# 1 it wo
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {wo, det}
gyùudanee dladahldagan
gyùudan-ee dladahlda-gan
horse-DEF fall.down-PST
`The horse fell down.'

# 2 it wo
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {wo}
dladahldagan gyùudanee
dladahlda-gan gyùudan-ee
fall.down-PST horse-DEF
`The horse fell down.'

# 3 tr wo
Source: a:75
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {wo}
ts’agts’aggee gyùudanee tlagaaydagan
ts’agts’ag-gee gyùudan-ee tlagaayda-gan
wagon-DEF horse-DEF get.injure-PST
`The wagon injured the horse.' or `The horse damaged the wagon.'

